## User Preferences

### Writing Style
- Introduction: short and focused, ~1 page
- Research Questions: paragraph format, NO sub-questions, NO validation pointers
- Forward references: PROHIBITED with concrete data (no "Table X in Section Y")
- Citations: always use `\cite{}` commands, never hardcoded numbers [15], [29]

### Content Decisions
- Abstract: COMRC structure (Context-Objective-Method-Results-Conclusions)
- Contributions: bullet list with metrics but minimal forward refs
- Related Work: critical positioning, not encyclopedic survey
- Threats: Wohlin et al. framework (4 categories)

